Nectopsyche pantostica
occurs in some Brazilian states in the southern and southeastern regions (
Henriques-Oliveira et al . 2019
;
Santos et al. 2020
). In the PNC, this species was collected in streams at different altitudes, and its presence is recorded for the first time in Espírito Santo state .

Neoathripsodes anomalus
is relatively abundant in the Atlantic Forest and has been recorded only in the Brazilian Southeastern Region (Dumas et al. 2009, 2012;
Paprocki & França 2014
). In the PNC, this species was collected in streams with small waterfalls and rocky bottom at altitudes above 1,000 m . This species is recorded for the first time for Espírito Santo state.
